node.contents: Can I add an option to force proguard to give every method a different name?

astNode.text: Can I add an option to force proguard to give every method a different name?

node.contents: Thank you for your answer. I've marked this correct because adding the line numbers has solved my issue. I did try -useuniqueclassmembernames but am I right in thinking this change makes all local variables unique, not methods? I still have many methods called 'a'.

astNode.text: Thank you for your answer. I've marked this correct because adding the line numbers has solved my issue. I did try -useuniqueclassmembernames but am I right in thinking this change makes all local variables unique, not methods? I still have many methods called 'a'.

node.contents: With -useuniqueclassmembernames, field names and method names that are different in the original code will also be different in the processed code, across all classes. This means that you may still see methods named 'a', but there should be fewer of them.
